{
  "answer": "The famous Ghalib couplet appears as the second *sher* (couplet) in ghazal #115 from *Diwan-E-Ghalib* (titled \"Koi ummeed bar nahin aati\"):\n\n**Original (Urdu):**  \nموت کا ایک دن معین ہے  \nنیند کیوں رات بھر نہیں آتی[^1]\n\n**Transliteration:**  \nMaut ka ek din muayyan hai  \nNeend kyun raat bhar nahin aati[^2]\n\n**Translation:**  \nOne day for death has been decreed;  \nSo why all night does sleep not come to me?[^3]\n\nThis reflects Ghalib's characteristic blend of existential anxiety and wry philosophy: death's inevitability is fixed (*muayyan*/decreed), so why the sleepless torment?[^4]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 115, [p-bd7a8e](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/115-koi-ummeed-bar-nahin-aati/original/#p-bd7a8e).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 115, [p-fda402](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/115-koi-ummeed-bar-nahin-aati/transliteration/#p-fda402).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 115, [p-e23971](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/115-koi-ummeed-bar-nahin-aati/translation/#p-e23971).\n\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 115 ([full chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/115-koi-ummeed-bar-nahin-aati/translation/)).",
